version: 1
display_name: PHTN-50-000013 - The Photon operating system must have the OpenSSL FIPS provider installed to protect the confidentiality of remote access sessions.
global_description: |-
  Without confidentiality protection mechanisms, unauthorized individuals may gain access to sensitive information via a remote access session.

  OpenSSH on the Photon operating system when configured appropriately can utilize a FIPS validated OpenSSL for cryptographic operations.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - PHTN-50-000013
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014
  cci:
    - CCI-000068
    - CCI-002418
    - CCI-002420
    - CCI-002422
    - CCI-002890
    - CCI-003123
  nist:
    - AC-17 (2)
    - MA-4 (6)
    - SC-8
    - SC-8 (2)
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_photon_5:
    type: custom
    desc: The Photon operating system must have the OpenSSL FIPS provider installed to protect the confidentiality of remote access sessions.
    control_id: PHTN-50-000013
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      At the command line, run the following command to verify the OpenSSL FIPS provider is installed:

      # rpm -qa | grep openssl-fips

      Example result:

      openssl-fips-provider-3.0.8-2.ph5.x86_64

      If there is no output indicating that the OpenSSL FIPS provider is installed, this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      Without confidentiality protection mechanisms, unauthorized individuals may gain access to sensitive information via a remote access session.

      OpenSSH on the Photon operating system when configured appropriately can utilize a FIPS validated OpenSSL for cryptographic operations.
    remediation: |-
      At the command line, run the following command:

      # tdnf install openssl-fips-provider
